The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the combinatorial optimization problem of finding the global minimum energy conformation in protein design. This involves integrating a heuristic function with the AND/OR branch-and-bound search algorithm. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as these are relevant to developing and integrating heuristic functions. The paper also involves optimization and combinatorial algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves testing on real protein data, which is relevant to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
